The paper discusses the application of the SP theory of intelligence to the management and analysis of big data, which involves topics such as unsupervised learning, pattern recognition, natural language processing, and reasoning. These topics are closely related to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of lossless compression for reducing the size of big data, which is a topic in database systems (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper mentions the parsing and production of natural language, which is a topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL), and the potential for high-parallel computing, which is a topic in computer architecture (cs.CC).
